  ğŸ“„ Description
  Pico y Placa Generator Special Edition is a Python-based tool designed to automate the creation 
of metadata for vehicle restriction zones, commonly known as â€œPico y Placaâ€, for this edition gives 
the coder the option to specify the restriction on a day-by-day basis based on the information collected.  
This tool simplifies the process by providing a graphical interface through Streamlit, allowing users to 
easily configure and generate restriction records without modifying the code. The tool exports the final 
data as a CSV file, which can be integrated into external vehicle control and monitoring systems.


ğŸš€ Features
âœ… User-friendly interface: Built with Streamlit for easy interaction.
âœ… Flexible restriction settings: Configure vehicle categories, date ranges, and restriction values.
âœ… Truck-specific restrictions: Option to add weight-based restrictions only when needed.
âœ… Holiday handling: Exclude holidays from the restriction periods.
âœ… Data export: Export the generated metadata to CSV format.
âœ… Duplicate prevention: Ensures no duplicate records are generated.
âœ… Open-source: Easily customizable for specific needs.

ğŸ”§ Installation
1ï¸âƒ£ Prerequisites
Make sure you have the following installed:

Python 3.x
Streamlit
Pandas
2ï¸âƒ£ Installation Steps
1 - Clone or download the repository:
git clone <repository_url>
cd Pico_y_Placa_Generator
Create a virtual environment (optional but recommended):
python -m venv venv
